If the corrosion is unfixable, the board may be unusable as a donor as well.  Try desoldering the mask ROM and cleaning up the pins with steel wool or something as best you can, then flux the crap out of them and resolder them back in.  It's at least worth a shot.  And if you still plan to use it as a donor anyway, at least it'd be good to check.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5348">qwertymodo</a> — Fri Jul 13, 2012 8:57 am</p><hr />
