<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9082&amp;p=96692#p96692"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Caveat: I have never made a SNES repro.<br /><br />My understanding is that odd-sized SNES games need to be padded as follows:<br />* take the first 2ⁿ bytes, where n is as large as possible (in this case, 2ⁿ=2MiB)<br />* take the remainder (which AFAIK is always 2ⁱ, i&lt;n), repeat that part 2⁽ⁿ¯ⁱ⁾  times<br />* result is an image 2ⁿ⁺¹ bytes in size.<br /></div><br /><br />Basically this, but then repeat the entire resulting file as necessary to fill the ROM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5348">qwertymodo</a> — Wed Jul 11, 2012 7:51 am</p><hr />
