<title type="html"><![CDATA[Dual Mask Rom cart to Single Mask Rom donor]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9082&amp;p=96684#p96684"><![CDATA[
Caveat: I have never made a SNES repro.<br /><br />My understanding is that odd-sized SNES games need to be padded as follows:<br />* take the first 2ⁿ bytes, where n is as large as possible (in this case, 2ⁿ=2MiB)<br />* take the remainder (which AFAIK is always 2ⁱ, i&lt;n), repeat that part 2⁽ⁿ¯ⁱ⁾  times<br />* result is an image 2ⁿ⁺¹ bytes in size.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Wed Jul 11, 2012 1:23 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
